<dl id="un1013g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013g"> (NLI.3) 13(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> = cult of Shakti, spouse of Siva, <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> dialogues between <mark>Shiva, the Great Yogin of the Gods, and his Shakti, Spouse or Power,</mark> Durg&amacr;. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The chief end of T&amacr;ntrika is the attainment of Power&mdash;that is the <mark>Cult of Shakti</mark>; this may be for a good or evil purpose and also according to a pure, or impure ritual. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#thrdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. M., &ldquo;Queries and Notes. VI&rdquo; 368</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Copied to <a name="s15021ak" href="s15all.htm#s15021ak">Sheet 15.021(ak)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 15.2271f. </mm> </dd></dl>
